DA notes the resignation of CEO, Paul Boughey The Democratic Alliance (DA) has accepted the resignation of its CEO, Paul Boughey. Paul has led the DA’s administration as CEO for close to five years, serving with distinction and an unflinching dedication to the party and South Africa.eval(ez_write_tag([[336,280],'politicsweb_co_za-box-3','ezslot_6',112,'0','0'])); We wish him all the best in his future endeavours and thank him for his service to the DA and commitment to the broader Democratic Project. The DA, grounded by its values of Freedom, Fairness, Opportunity and Diversity, remains committed to building one party with one prosperous future for all South Africans. The resignation letter can be found here.eval(ez_write_tag([[580,400],'politicsweb_co_za-medrectangle-3','ezslot_5',113,'0','0'])); Issued by Solly Malatsi, DA National Spokesperson, 17 October 2019